item.content:encoded:
I was puzzled when rumors circulated that Vans was going to rebuild the Combi pool. Trying to replicate a legendary icon such as the Combi brings all sorts of challenges – I thought it may be better to keep all the fear, fun and pain that the original Combi generated in the memory bank. Plus, I had a hard time visualizing how they would fit this massive pool inside a warehouse. As a kid, the original Combi seemed to take up acres of space.

Once the Vans version was completed, all of my reservations were tossed to the side. The new Combi was a blast to ride from the very first run. And while the dimensions were different, you could instantly feel/try the same lines that the Pipeline Combi offered. The original Combi was unique in that it allowed you to do some tricks on hips, corners or odd walls – places where you  just never would try a certain trick for a number of reasons. But I instantly saw skaters do tricks from the old pool in those same spots in the Vans Combi – it was a Twilight Zone moment!

Since lines are the name of the game in this pool, you need to be able to cut quickly and that Vans Combi plaster could really kill you. Once Vans refurbished it a few years back, the new pool became the most epic pool ever built in my opinion. Filling-in the channel opened up the shallow end and the stickier cement surface allowed you to generate speed and make cuts to any wall you wanted.

The early Pro-Tec Pool Party contests were really just fun jams and sessions. Everyone was so stoked to be skating this great pool with your friends and seeing everybody rip. The energy level was straight through the roof. I don't recall such a cool and fun atmosphere at a contest...EVER! I love the fact you can watch two skaters do the exact same run but see totally different styles. The Combi is an open canvas for each skater that drops in, allowing for creativity, flair and style. Over the last few years, there has been a huge influx of new blood at the Pool Party. Seeing young skaters grow up in this pool and now ripping the Pool Party is really inspiring for vert skateboarding.

