William Sharp and I are proud to announce that after three and a half long years, we've signed contracts with Gingko Press of Berkeley, California. The William Sharp photographic book contains previously unpublished images from the groundbreaking years of skateboarding's growth, spanning 1976 through 1980. Photographs of the desert pipes in Arizona, Mt. Baldy pipe, schoolyards, banks, ditches, pools and the early contest series are all included with anecdotes from the riders who were there. This is a historical vision. A look into not an area... but an all-encompassing look into an era. An era that can never happen again. The book will be hardcover, 11 1/2  X 13 inches and will be available this fall in bookstores.

